race.comment: Good race the 3YO feature and I'm going with HEEZA PHOENIX (1) despite the wide draw. There are a couple knocks, including a disappointing start last time, though he's trialled well since. Drawn out, but he's the best horse in the race and that hold plenty of weight under these conditions. TWISTED STEEL (3) was too good against his own age last time out, sitting up front and getting the job done with ease. That form has already been franked and he has the speed to roll across from a tricky draw. Makes plenty of appeal in a race with a long tail. MAJOR FLIRT (6) just missed over 1400m two back before finding them a bit quick over 1000m last time out. Back out to 1200m is a big tick here and there's a strong case for him at good odds. SOUND OF SPEED (4) is racing in good order and is not to be discounted on the quick turnaround. MARDUSA (5) will be fitter for the fresh run and can storm home down the outside under Pike.
